Jenni Evans, News24(Netcare 911) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Two men sustained severe burns while working on an electrical transformer at a university in Roodepoort on Sunday night, Netcare 911 said.One man sustained 50% burns and the other 20% burns when a ''flash over'' - a burst of very high energy - occurred. Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha said the men had to be stabilised on the scene before one of them was taken to hospital by helicopter, and the other by ambulance.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.